{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":444,"text":"We are losing our listening."},{"time":3499,"text":"We spend roughly 60 percent\nof our communication time listening,"},{"time":7444,"text":"but we're not very good at it."},{"time":9000,"text":"We retain just 25 percent of what we hear."},{"time":11531,"text":"Now -- not you, not this talk,"},{"time":13057,"text":"but that is generally true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":14606,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":16025,"text":"Let's define listening\nas making meaning from sound."},{"time":19632,"text":"It's a mental process,"},{"time":21235,"text":"and it's a process of extraction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23885,"text":"We use some pretty cool\ntechniques to do this."},{"time":26070,"text":"One of them is pattern recognition."},{"time":27833,"text":"(Crowd noises) So in a cocktail\nparty like this,"},{"time":30209,"text":"if I say, \"David, Sara, pay attention\" --\nsome of you just sat up."},{"time":34518,"text":"We recognize patterns\nto distinguish noise from signal,"},{"time":38211,"text":"and especially our name."},{"time":40251,"text":"Differencing is another technique we use."},{"time":42314,"text":"If I left this pink noise on\nfor more than a couple of minutes,"},{"time":45494,"text":"(Pink noise) you would literally\ncease to hear it."},{"time":48092,"text":"We listen to differences;\nwe discount sounds that remain the same."}]},{"cues":[{"time":53052,"text":"And then there is a whole\nrange of filters."},{"time":55865,"text":"These filters take us from all sound"},{"time":58341,"text":"down to what we pay attention to."},{"time":60436,"text":"Most people are entirely\nunconscious of these filters."},{"time":64519,"text":"But they actually create\nour reality in a way,"},{"time":67093,"text":"because they tell us what\nwe're paying attention to right now."},{"time":70124,"text":"I'll give you one example of that."},{"time":71914,"text":"Intention is very important\nin sound, in listening."},{"time":75234,"text":"When I married my wife,"},{"time":77000,"text":"I promised her I would listen\nto her every day"},{"time":79684,"text":"as if for the first time."},{"time":81970,"text":"Now that's something\nI fall short of on a daily basis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85250,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":86287,"text":"But it's a great intention\nto have in a relationship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88909,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":90618,"text":"But that's not all."},{"time":91793,"text":"Sound places us in space and in time."},{"time":94769,"text":"If you close your eyes\nright now in this room,"},{"time":97722,"text":"you're aware of the size of the room"},{"time":99753,"text":"from the reverberation and the bouncing\nof the sound off the surfaces;"},{"time":103595,"text":"you're aware of how many\npeople are around you,"},{"time":105886,"text":"because of the micro-noises\nyou're receiving."},{"time":108505,"text":"And sound places us in time as well,"},{"time":111112,"text":"because sound always has\ntime embedded in it."},{"time":114596,"text":"In fact, I would suggest\nthat our listening is the main way"},{"time":117542,"text":"that we experience the flow of time"},{"time":119712,"text":"from past to future."},{"time":121809,"text":"So, \"Sonority is time\nand meaning\" -- a great quote."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124759,"text":"I said at the beginning,\nwe're losing our listening."},{"time":127224,"text":"Why did I say that?"},{"time":128658,"text":"Well, there are a lot of reasons for this."},{"time":130716,"text":"First of all, we invented\nways of recording --"},{"time":132945,"text":"first writing, then audio recording\nand now video recording as well."},{"time":136711,"text":"The premium on accurate and careful\nlistening has simply disappeared."},{"time":141415,"text":"Secondly, the world is now so noisy,"},{"time":144000,"text":"(Noise) with this cacophony\ngoing on visually and auditorily,"},{"time":149000,"text":"it's just hard to listen;"},{"time":151000,"text":"it's tiring to listen."},{"time":153166,"text":"Many people take refuge in headphones,"},{"time":155639,"text":"but they turn big,\npublic spaces like this,"},{"time":158716,"text":"shared soundscapes,"},{"time":160136,"text":"into millions of tiny,\nlittle personal sound bubbles."},{"time":164570,"text":"In this scenario,\nnobody's listening to anybody."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167887,"text":"We're becoming impatient."},{"time":169958,"text":"We don't want oratory anymore;\nwe want sound bites."},{"time":173000,"text":"And the art of conversation is being\nreplaced -- dangerously, I think --"},{"time":177469,"text":"by personal broadcasting."},{"time":179480,"text":"I don't know how much listening\nthere is in this conversation,"},{"time":182971,"text":"which is sadly very common,\nespecially in the UK."},{"time":186455,"text":"We're becoming desensitized."},{"time":188150,"text":"Our media have to scream at us\nwith these kinds of headlines"},{"time":191629,"text":"in order to get our attention."},{"time":193621,"text":"And that means it's harder\nfor us to pay attention"},{"time":196076,"text":"to the quiet, the subtle, the understated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200327,"text":"This is a serious problem\nthat we're losing our listening."},{"time":203272,"text":"This is not trivial,"},{"time":205263,"text":"because listening is our access\nto understanding."},{"time":208966,"text":"Conscious listening\nalways creates understanding,"},{"time":212451,"text":"and only without conscious listening"},{"time":215105,"text":"can these things happen."},{"time":217000,"text":"A world where we don't listen\nto each other at all"},{"time":219986,"text":"is a very scary place indeed."},{"time":223754,"text":"So I'd like to share with you\nfive simple exercises,"},{"time":227100,"text":"tools you can take away with you,"},{"time":228814,"text":"to improve your own conscious listening."},{"time":231030,"text":"Would you like that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":232210,"text":"Audience: Yes!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":233400,"text":"Good. The first one is silence."},{"time":236352,"text":"Just three minutes a day of silence\nis a wonderful exercise"},{"time":240000,"text":"to reset your ears and to recalibrate,"},{"time":242736,"text":"so that you can hear the quiet again."},{"time":244863,"text":"If you can't get absolute silence,"},{"time":246562,"text":"go for quiet, that's absolutely fine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249563,"text":"Second, I call this \"the mixer.\""},{"time":252260,"text":"(Noise) So even if you're\nin a noisy environment like this --"},{"time":255773,"text":"and we all spend a lot of time\nin places like this --"},{"time":258522,"text":"listen in the coffee bar\nto how many channels of sound can I hear?"},{"time":262618,"text":"How many individual channels\nin that mix am I listening to?"},{"time":265600,"text":"You can do it in a beautiful place\nas well, like in a lake."},{"time":268838,"text":"How many birds am I hearing?"},{"time":270349,"text":"Where are they? Where are those ripples?"},{"time":272579,"text":"It's a great exercise for improving\nthe quality of your listening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277196,"text":"Third, this exercise I call \"savoring,\"\nand this is a beautiful exercise."},{"time":281000,"text":"It's about enjoying mundane sounds."},{"time":283000,"text":"This, for example, is my tumble dryer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286253,"text":"(Dryer)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":287375,"text":"It's a waltz -- one, two, three;\none, two, three; one, two, three."},{"time":291881,"text":"I love it!"},{"time":293127,"text":"Or just try this one on for size."}]},{"cues":[{"time":295323,"text":"(Coffee grinder)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":304453,"text":"Wow!"},{"time":306000,"text":"So, mundane sounds\ncan be really interesting --"},{"time":308403,"text":"if you pay attention."},{"time":309620,"text":"I call that the \"hidden choir\" --\nit's around us all the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313134,"text":"The next exercise is probably\nthe most important of all of these,"},{"time":316981,"text":"if you just take one thing away."},{"time":318676,"text":"This is listening positions --"},{"time":320321,"text":"the idea that you can move\nyour listening position"},{"time":323800,"text":"to what's appropriate\nto what you're listening to."},{"time":326639,"text":"This is playing with those filters."},{"time":328409,"text":"Remember I gave you those filters?"},{"time":330087,"text":"It's starting to play with them as levers,"},{"time":332138,"text":"to get conscious about them\nand to move to different places."},{"time":335039,"text":"These are just some\nof the listening positions,"},{"time":337302,"text":"or scales of listening\npositions, that you can use."},{"time":339733,"text":"There are many."},{"time":340923,"text":"Have fun with that. It's very exciting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343425,"text":"And finally, an acronym."},{"time":345551,"text":"You can use this in listening,\nin communication."},{"time":348470,"text":"If you're in any one of those roles --"},{"time":350710,"text":"and I think that probably is everybody\nwho's listening to this talk --"},{"time":354505,"text":"the acronym is RASA,"},{"time":356212,"text":"which is the Sanskrit word\nfor \"juice\" or \"essence.\""},{"time":360243,"text":"And RASA stands for \"Receive,\"\nwhich means pay attention to the person;"},{"time":365076,"text":"\"Appreciate,\" making little noises\nlike \"hmm,\" \"oh,\" \"OK\";"},{"time":368502,"text":"\"Summarize\" -- the word \"so\"\nis very important in communication;"},{"time":371913,"text":"and \"Ask,\" ask questions afterwards."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375000,"text":"Now sound is my passion, it's my life."},{"time":377316,"text":"I wrote a whole book about it.\nSo I live to listen."},{"time":379874,"text":"That's too much to ask for most people."},{"time":382754,"text":"But I believe that every human being\nneeds to listen consciously"},{"time":386725,"text":"in order to live fully --"},{"time":388855,"text":"connected in space and in time\nto the physical world around us,"},{"time":392569,"text":"connected in understanding to each other,"},{"time":395119,"text":"not to mention spiritually connected,"},{"time":396965,"text":"because every spiritual path\nI know of has listening and contemplation"},{"time":400801,"text":"at its heart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402650,"text":"That's why we need to teach listening\nin our schools as a skill."},{"time":408517,"text":"Why is it not taught? It's crazy."},{"time":410914,"text":"And if we can teach listening\nin our schools,"},{"time":413397,"text":"we can take our listening\noff that slippery slope"},{"time":416159,"text":"to that dangerous, scary world\nthat I talked about,"},{"time":418729,"text":"and move it to a place where everybody\nis consciously listening all the time,"},{"time":422481,"text":"or at least capable of doing it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424285,"text":"Now, I don't know how to do that,"},{"time":426190,"text":"but this is TED,"},{"time":428187,"text":"and I think the TED community\nis capable of anything."},{"time":431281,"text":"So I invite you to connect with me,\nconnect with each other,"},{"time":434565,"text":"take this mission out."},{"time":435794,"text":"And let's get listening taught in schools,"},{"time":437871,"text":"and transform the world in one generation"},{"time":439893,"text":"to a conscious, listening world --\na world of connection,"},{"time":442639,"text":"a world of understanding"},{"time":444000,"text":"and a world of peace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445650,"text":"Thank you for listening to me today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447429,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}